Based on clinical studies reported to date, the following factors may affect or be associated with the prognosis of COVID-19 patients (Table 33):
Age: Age was the most important factor in determining the prognosis for SARS, which is also true for COVID-19.
The age group of 30 to 65 years was primarily affected by COVID-19, with 47.7% of these patients over the age of 50 in a study of 8,866 cases as described above.
