It has been reported that SARS-CoV-2 can also bind to positive bile cells with the angiotensin-converting enzyme 2, which may lead to liver dysfunction in COVID-19 patients.
It should be noted that age and underlying disease are strongly linked and may overlap.
Abnormal laboratory results: The level of CRP in the blood reflects the severity of inflammation or tissue injury, and has been suggested to be a predictor of disease, response to treatment, and eventual recovery.
