Australia 's stores are lowering their toilet paper limits per transaction .
Australian department store chains Wallworths and Coles on Saturday and Sunday evening tightened restrictions on toilet paper purchases to reduce them to two rolls from Wallworths and one roll from Coles per transaction at all branches nationwide.
I also set up Aldi's stores for one bubble, and that was on Monday.
